<p>So the first part of the question is easy: how to pass a parameter from JSF page to backing bean. <a href="http://www.mkyong.com/jsf2/4-ways-to-pass-parameter-from-jsf-page-to-backing-bean/" rel="nofollow">This page</a> answers the question.</p>  <p>The second part is the via Button and ConfirmDialog. Let me show you what I mean with that.<br> I have a Button:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;p:commandButton id="deleteStuff" oncomplete="PF('askIfSure').show()" styleClass="actionButton searchResult" value="#{Msgs.digipflege$delete}"                  rendered="#{securityService.isCallerInRole(UserRole.ADMIN)}"&gt;    &lt;f:param name="usage_id" value="#{item.id}"/&gt; &lt;/p:commandButton&gt; </code></pre>  <p>And then I have the ConfirmDialog which then opens the Bean-Method:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;p:confirmDialog message="#{Msgs.digipflege$question_delete}" header="#{Msgs.digipflege$delete_secure}" action="#{fotoDetailController.deleteUsage}" severity="alert" widgetVar="cd_usage_delete" appendTo="@(body)"&gt; &lt;h:form id="confirmDelete"&gt;     &lt;p:commandButton value="#{Msgs.digipflege$delete}" oncomplete="PF('askIfSure').hide()" update=":fotoForm"/&gt;     &lt;p:commandButton value="#{Msgs.digipflege$cancel}" onclick="PF('askIfSure').hide();" type="button" /&gt; &lt;/h:form&gt; </code></pre>  <p></p>  <p>So now the <strong>problem</strong> is that <code>&lt;f:param name="usage_id" value="#{item.id}"/&gt;</code> is never called... I also tryed it with a f:setPropertyActionListener  but it also doesn't get called. How should I do it?</p>  <hr>  <p>PS: With this solution I take the parameter with.</p>  <pre><code>Map&lt;String,String&gt; params = FacesContext.getCurrentInstance().getExternalContext().getRequestParameterMap(); </code></pre>